FBIS3-16165 "drsov049_b_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Chernomyrdin Makes Ministerial Appointments LD1403095694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0926 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403095694 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS] [Text] Moscow March 14 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin appointed Aleksandr Vronts Russian deputy communications minister, says a resolution which came to ITAR-TASS today. Viktor Chernomyrdin signed a decree appointing Yuriy Portnov chairman of the Russian Federation's Committee for Affairs of the Youth, Physical Culture and Tourism. Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin appointed Vladimir Volodin first deputy chairman of the Russian Committee for the Press. Sergey Gryzunov and Andrey Chernenko were appointed deputy chairmen of this committee, says a resolution of the Russian Government which came to ITAR-TASS today.
